You can use zsh or bash for git.

Follow the instruction to download GIT.
https://git-scm.com/downloads

Check Git version:
git --version

config git:
git config --global --user.name "Jack-Chau"
git config --global --user.email "xxxxx@gmail.com"

check configuration:
git config -l 

go to the directory that you want to upload to git repository
git init .

check git status and those file have not uoloaded on git repository
git status

*** Staging Area ***
add file
git add <filen ame>

remove file from repository
git rm --cached <file name>

remove all file:
git rm -r --cached ./

*** Commit files to commit history ***
git commit -m "<file name>"

see log: (you can see the hash here)
git log

git show <hash>

Diff the different between differernt submission
git diff

For upload file to github
https://docs.github.com/en/authentication/connecting-to-github-with-ssh/generating-a-new-ssh-key-and-adding-it-to-the-ssh-agent







